      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds good in theory, but who gets to decide what a \"core tenet\" is? if every group just claims their preference is a \"sincere religious belief,\" it feels like the law just becomes a suggestion. isn't it more fair if the law applies to everyone equally, regardless of what they believe? it seems like giving them an out just makes the secular state weaker and less reliable for everyone else.",
